				p Each one of these files link to a separate css that helps obtain the functionality of that specific component. If you do not need a specific component; for example, the Slider component, on your website, then feel free to delete the <span class="code-div">@import</span> line linking to the slider.css file. By deleting a line from the liger css file, you are making this css file size smaller, which is a good thing. 		
				p The first file in the list is a link to Font Awesome. Liger uses Font Awesome's CDN in order to aid in some of Liger's animations for its animated form. 

